<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE suite SYSTEM "https://testng.org/testng-1.0.dtd">
<!--
    thread-count is deliberately 2, not 3 - it must not exceed the actual
    concurrent session capacity of the Grid it's running against.

    In this project's docker-compose.yml / CI workflow, one chrome-node
    container is started with SE_NODE_MAX_SESSIONS=2, so total chrome
    capacity is 1 node x 2 sessions = 2 concurrent sessions. Requesting a
    3rd session from a 3rd TestNG thread on a resource-constrained CI runner
    can starve the container (CPU/RAM) badly enough that an in-progress
    Chrome session dies mid-test - that's what a NoSuchSessionException
    actually means (the session is gone), as opposed to a
    StaleElementReferenceException (session is fine, DOM just changed under
    an old element reference). This is a real failure this project hit:
    thread-count=3 against a 2-session-capacity node caused exactly this.

    parallel="methods" is still correct and still requires DriverFactory's
    ThreadLocal - that reasoning doesn't change. Only the thread COUNT
    needed to change, to match infrastructure capacity rather than be
    picked arbitrarily.

    If you scale chrome-node/firefox-node up (more replicas or higher
    SE_NODE_MAX_SESSIONS), thread-count can safely go up to match.
-->
<suite name="GridSuite" parallel="methods" thread-count="2">
    <test name="RegressionTests">
        <classes>
            <class name="com.tests.LoginTest"/>
            <class name="com.tests.DropdownTest"/>
            <class name="com.tests.CheckboxTest"/>
        </classes>
    </test>
</suite>